---
import AppLayout from "../../../layouts/AppLayout.astro";
---

<AppLayout
  title="Grimora Support"
  description="Support resources for Grimora, including bug reports, feature requests, data issues, and App Store review contact."
  currentPath="/apps/grimora/support"
>
  <article class="contentPage">
    <header class="contentPageHeader">
      <p class="eyebrow">Grimora</p>
      <h1>Support</h1>
      <p class="contentIntro">
        Use GitHub Issues for Grimora support, bug reports, feature requests,
        and data or image issues.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>GitHub Issues</h2>
      <p>
        The support inbox for Grimora is the public issue tracker on GitHub:
        <a href="https://github.com/SamBWagner/Grimora/issues">github.com/SamBWagner/Grimora/issues</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Please include your platform, app version, what you expected to happen,
        what happened instead, and any steps that reproduce the issue.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Bug Reports</h2>
      <p>
        For crashes, broken sync behavior, search problems, or layout issues,
        open a GitHub issue with screenshots or screen recordings when they help
        explain the problem.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Feature Requests</h2>
      <p>
        For new search workflows, list-building tools, platform improvements,
        or quality-of-life ideas, open a feature request in GitHub Issues.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Data And Image Issues</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora uses Scryfall and MTGJSON data. If a card, printing, price, or
        image looks wrong in Grimora, report it with the card name, set code,
        collector number, and a short description of what appears incorrect.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>App Store Review Contact</h2>
      <p>
        App Store review questions can also be filed through the same GitHub
        issue tracker. Mention that the report is for App Store review so it can
        be handled quickly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Account Safety</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora has no sign-in system. Support should never ask for your
        password, private Apple ID details, iCloud credentials, or payment
        details. Do not post sensitive personal information in public issues.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</AppLayout>
